justification: The fields 'name', 'taskType', 'taskCode', 'taskDefinitionVersion', 'taskGroupPriority', 'firstSubmitTime', 'submitTime', 'startTime', 'endTime', 'host', 'executePath', 'logPath', 'retryTimes', 'pid', 'appLink', 'duration', 'maxRetryTimes', 'retryInterval', 'workerGroup', 'environmentCode', 'environmentConfig', 'executorId', 'varPool', 'executorName', 'delayTime', 'taskParams', 'dryRun', 'taskGroupId', 'cpuQuota', and 'memoryMax' are repeated across the 'TaskInstance' class and the 'TaskInstanceExecuteDto' class. Extracting these fields into a separate domain class can encapsulate the task instance properties and reduce the duplication between the data transfer object and the entity.
